The moonlight shone coolly, and the air filled with frost; The long night approached, yet the will to light was never lost."

"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The iron ring worn by Clive.
Alas, the abyss looms nigh. Proceed, and let darkness consume thee; Retreat, and let fear erode thy soul."

600321.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A leather helmet sewn from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blood Beast.

600322.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A leather jacket sewn from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.

600323.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> A ring crafted from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The bone smith who crafted this became haunted for seven nights, by horrific cries wailing in the darkness."

600324.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Amulet crafted from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.

600331.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The dark iron helmet of Baphomet the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
Blood represents the gravity of memory, while souls are as free as the blue sky. It's not that they are grander, just less attached."

600332.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The heavy plate armor of Baphomet, the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"I gave up my body in pursuit of immortality, only to realize that the soul also ages.""

600333.m_mEquipDesc:

600512.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Goldland's silk white shirt, completely spotless.
Though his elegance and grandeur may not be genuine, the effort placed into preserving purity is appreciable."

600513.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Goldland's golden ring, symbolizing wealth and status.
It represents the lofty status of the Landis family. From material to craftsmanship, it perfectly complements its current owner, and yet not once has he worn it."

600514.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Jewelry that never left Goldland's possession.
"Listen. This is all I have to leave you with. Adorn it, and seek your own freedom.""

600521.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
A sheer veil masks her gaze, yet fails to conceal the icy tear streaming down her cheek."

600522.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
Silken scaly wings drape over your shoulders and gently brush against your skin, providing you with a faint sense of solace."

600523.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Though Sheila the Firstborn's form has long since disintegrated, her icy ring still remains, imbued with the primal power of Plague.
The broken corpse marks the end of a cycle, while the ring heralds its dawn. "Abandoning the past shall lead to nowhere.""

600524.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Sheila the Firstborn's figure dissipated, thus breaking her final set of wings. It contains the primal power of Plague.
"Facing the abyss, I leap forward, if only to fill the chasms blocking your path ahead.""

600531.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the crown of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
Cupping it in your palm, you lean in to listen, nearly making out the roar of the ocean. There seems to be a voice, too, but it is muffled by the foam."

600532.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the shattered scales of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
Bathed in the silver light of the moon, it seems one can glimpse a sorrowful past, or some unreachable distance, hidden in their luster."

600533.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The hardened tentacle tips of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, which retain the primal power of "Famine."
Reaching out to touch the light could be the path towards hope, or perhaps the start of an endless Abyss."

600534.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> A dorsal fin taken from Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, imbued with the primal power of "Famine."

600712.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Piera, stitched ornately.
Carefully, she collects the sorrows of the dead, folding each piece meticulously then stacking them on her shoulder, waiting for the pain to absorb into her."

600713.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Piera's cherished ring, seemingly symbolizing a pact made with someone.
Could internalizing one's pain be a form of deceit?"

600714.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Piera's collection of skulls, her constant companions.
Pristine white bones, each a testament to the girl's acts of redemption. She convinces herself this is a form of kindness."

600721.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The stylish cap worn by Isaac Van Helsing. On the pursuit of justice, it shielded him from the elements.
Though the damp winds may tousle his hair, they are incapable of extinguishing the youthful sparkle in his eyes."

600722.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The pauldrons worn by Van Helsing. Its bold design accentuates the wearer's personality.
At the time, he hadn't realized that pursuing one's vision demands bearing heavy responsibility."

600723.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Van Helsing's wrist guard, stained with blood.
Even as the marsh envelops his figure, the young man draws his sword with swift alacrity, displaying not even a speck of hesitation."

600724.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Van Helsing's vows echoed with resolve.
It wasn't until darkness consumed him that he realized: Only actions taken from a position of power are considered true justice."

600731.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A veil worn by Ressa resembling that of a typical clergywoman, yet it holds a deeper meaning for her.
She ceaselessly smooths, folds, and tucks the edges into her white cap until the Bell of Tempus tolls."

600732.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Ressa Ambolia. It accompanied her over the long days and nights of separation, as she awaited someone's return.
Moonlight, gentle yet somewhat duplicitous, bathes her as she leans against the window, shedding tears, just as scripted."

600733.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Ressa's cherished promise ring, seemingly worn for ages.
The tiny silver ring worn on the middle finger silently declares love, yet by dawn, it becomes a shackle."

600734.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Ressa's cherished memories, strung together by countless moments of happiness.
In the end, the happiness they defended so vigorously was merely a ruse of fate, designed to trap them in the present."

600912.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The black robe of Agares the Beguiler, which suppresses his high-temperature scales. It is imbued with the primal power of War.
As the Flaming Chariot raced across the sky, he removed one of his own ribs, using it as kindling to cast the first ray of light."

600913.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> A ring forged from the blood of Agares the Beguiler, imbued with the primal power of War.
Iron nails pierced the chest, and hot blood stained the mountainside. Gazing down at the smoke billowing in mortal realms, he finally found solace as he closed his eyes."

600914.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Agares the Beguiler, after being consumed by flames, left only a few feathers as proof of his existence in this world.
As he opens his eyes once more, wings grew from his spine, and his hunger drove him to gorge on entrails. Alas, he was never a hero, but a vulture who drank the blood of heroic memories."

600921.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The feathered crown discarded by Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
Renouncing himself to embrace death, his sole hope is to leave a trace of himself somewhere in the future."

600922.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The torn garment of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
The fervor which burned inside chest was not for the present, but for a future unbound from destiny."

600923.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring.</style> A ring forged from the blood of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
Blood and mind converged to birth a soul which could lead them forth. "This is faith; overbearing, yet ethereal.""

600924.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The amalgamation of deep despair and profound hope within Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
'Place down your sword, the future you seek is not elsewhere; it is right beneath your feet.'"

600931.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A crown that embodies Joan's resolve.
War is the lifeblood of civilization. Flowing through the corridors of history, it is unstoppable, nay inevitable."

600932.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A blood-stained suit of armor worn by Joan.
Leaning against the wall, the homeland lay behind her in ruins; gazing into the distance, the future lay before her in doubt."

600933.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Joan's signet ring, shaped like twin-peaks and engraved with the words "May Astolfo remain prosperous."
She leads all the lost souls unable to return home to the Motherland of nigh. "Through utter despair, hope springs anew.""

600934.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Joan's immortal past.
"Though yesterday has vanished and tomorrow is already known, how ought one navigate today?""

"Children say I look scary, but admire me in battle. So I keep this thing on for them, I suppose. Until the grave calls me.""

601412.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The robe that Clive often wore.
The moonlight shone coolly, and the air filled with frost; The long night approached, yet the will to light was never lost."

601413.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The iron ring worn by Clive.
Alas, the abyss looms nigh. Proceed, and let darkness consume thee; Retreat, and let fear erode thy soul."

601421.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A leather helmet sewn from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blood Beast.
Perhaps an illusion? The visage revealed by this Blackblood Beast appears to be in agony, yet somehow gives the impression of a grin."

601422.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A leather jacket sewn from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.

601423.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> A ring crafted from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The bone smith who crafted this became haunted for seven nights, by horrific cries wailing in the darkness."

601424.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Amulet crafted from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The Bell Ringer melted the beast's seemingly impregnable hide instantaneously with a terrible heat, bringing inspiration to the artisans."

601431.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The dark iron helmet of Baphomet the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
Blood represents the gravity of memory, while souls are as free as the blue sky. It's not that they are grander, just less attached."

601432.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The heavy plate armor of Baphomet, the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"I gave up my body in pursuit of immortality, only to realize that the soul also ages.""

601433.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The dark iron ring of Baphomet the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"Once again, I find myself at your mercy. Perhaps this time, I should try finding credence in that distant prophecy?""

601434.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The rusty amulet of Baphomet, the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"Ashes beget ashes, and dust begets dust. Alas, life is but an anomaly, and all living memory perishes.""

601511.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Goldland's stylish cravat, clean and exquisite.
It still retains a faint scent, one that seemingly blends beauty and maturity."

601512.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Goldland's silk white shirt, completely spotless.
Though his elegance and grandeur may not be genuine, the effort placed into preserving purity is appreciable."

601513.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Goldland's golden ring, symbolizing wealth and status.
It represents the lofty status of the Landis family. From material to craftsmanship, it perfectly complements its current owner, and yet not once has he worn it."

601514.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Jewelry that never left Goldland's possession.
"Listen. This is all I have to leave you with. Adorn it, and seek your own freedom.""

601521.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
A sheer veil masks her gaze, yet fails to conceal the icy tear streaming down her cheek."

601522.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
Silken scaly wings drape over your shoulders and gently brush against your skin, providing you with a faint sense of solace."

601523.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Though Sheila the Firstborn's form has long since disintegrated, her icy ring still remains, imbued with the primal power of Plague.
The broken corpse marks the end of a cycle, while the ring heralds its dawn. "Abandoning the past shall lead to nowhere.""

601524.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Sheila the Firstborn's figure dissipated, thus breaking her final set of wings. It contains the primal power of Plague.
"Facing the abyss, I leap forward, if only to fill the chasms blocking your path ahead.""

601531.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the crown of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."

601532.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the shattered scales of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
Bathed in the silver light of the moon, it seems one can glimpse a sorrowful past, or some unreachable distance, hidden in their luster."

601533.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The hardened tentacle tips of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, which retain the primal power of "Famine."
Reaching out to touch the light could be the path towards hope, or perhaps the start of an endless Abyss."

601712.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Piera, stitched ornately.
Carefully, she collects the sorrows of the dead, folding each piece meticulously then stacking them on her shoulder, waiting for the pain to absorb into her."

601713.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Piera's cherished ring, seemingly symbolizing a pact made with someone.
Could internalizing one's pain be a form of deceit?"

601714.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Piera's collection of skulls, her constant companions.
Pristine white bones, each a testament to the girl's acts of redemption. She convinces herself this is a form of kindness."

601721.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The stylish cap worn by Isaac Van Helsing. On the pursuit of justice, it shielded him from the elements.
Though the damp winds may tousle his hair, they are incapable of extinguishing the youthful sparkle in his eyes."

601722.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The pauldrons worn by Van Helsing. Its bold design accentuates the wearer's personality.
At the time, he hadn't realized that pursuing one's vision demands bearing heavy responsibility."

601723.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Van Helsing's wrist guard, stained with blood.
Even as the marsh envelops his figure, the young man draws his sword with swift alacrity, displaying not even a speck of hesitation."

601724.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Van Helsing's vows echoed with resolve.
It wasn't until darkness consumed him that he realized: Only actions taken from a position of power are considered true justice."

601731.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A veil worn by Ressa resembling that of a typical clergywoman, yet it holds a deeper meaning for her.
She ceaselessly smooths, folds, and tucks the edges into her white cap until the Bell of Tempus tolls."

601732.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Ressa Ambolia. It accompanied her over the long days and nights of separation, as she awaited someone's return.
Moonlight, gentle yet somewhat duplicitous, bathes her as she leans against the window, shedding tears, just as scripted."

601733.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Ressa's cherished promise ring, seemingly worn for ages.
The tiny silver ring worn on the middle finger silently declares love, yet by dawn, it becomes a shackle."

601734.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Ressa's cherished memories, strung together by countless moments of happiness.
In the end, the happiness they defended so vigorously was merely a ruse of fate, designed to trap them in the present."

601913.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> A ring forged from the blood of Agares the Beguiler, imbued with the primal power of War.
Iron nails pierced the chest, and hot blood stained the mountainside. Gazing down at the smoke billowing in mortal realms, he finally found solace as he closed his eyes."

601914.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Agares the Beguiler, after being consumed by flames, left only a few feathers as proof of his existence in this world.
As he opens his eyes once more, wings grew from his spine, and his hunger drove him to gorge on entrails. Alas, he was never a hero, but a vulture who drank the blood of heroic memories."

601921.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The feathered crown discarded by Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
Renouncing himself to embrace death, his sole hope is to leave a trace of himself somewhere in the future."

601922.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The torn garment of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.

601923.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring.</style> A ring forged from the blood of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.

601924.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The amalgamation of deep despair and profound hope within Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
'Place down your sword, the future you seek is not elsewhere; it is right beneath your feet.'"

601931.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A crown that embodies Joan's resolve.
War is the lifeblood of civilization. Flowing through the corridors of history, it is unstoppable, nay inevitable."

601932.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A blood-stained suit of armor worn by Joan.
Leaning against the wall, the homeland lay behind her in ruins; gazing into the distance, the future lay before her in doubt."

601933.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Joan's signet ring, shaped like twin-peaks and engraved with the words "May Astolfo remain prosperous."
She leads all the lost souls unable to return home to the Motherland of nigh. "Through utter despair, hope springs anew.""

601934.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Joan's immortal past.
"Though yesterday has vanished and tomorrow is already known, how ought one navigate today?""

Cupping it in your palm, you lean in to listen, nearly making out the roar of the ocean. There seems to be a voice, too, but it is muffled by the foam."

602632.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the shattered scales of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
Bathed in the silver light of the moon, it seems one can glimpse a sorrowful past, or some unreachable distance, hidden in their luster."

602633.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The hardened tentacle tips of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, which retain the primal power of "Famine."
Reaching out to touch the light could be the path towards hope, or perhaps the start of an endless Abyss."

602634.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> A dorsal fin taken from Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
'Facing the boundless sea, the shackles on my back deny me my only possession — freedom. And yet I embrace them willingly.'"

602711.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A headpiece worn by Piera that emanates a lambent glow.
Silk ribbons embroider the restless mind of the Bone Collector. Pray tell me, are white lies truly kind, or are they deception?"

602712.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Piera, stitched ornately.
Carefully, she collects the sorrows of the dead, folding each piece meticulously then stacking them on her shoulder, waiting for the pain to absorb into her."

602713.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Piera's cherished ring, seemingly symbolizing a pact made with someone.
Could internalizing one's pain be a form of deceit?"

602714.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Piera's collection of skulls, her constant companions.
Pristine white bones, each a testament to the girl's acts of redemption. She convinces herself this is a form of kindness."

602721.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The stylish cap worn by Isaac Van Helsing. On the pursuit of justice, it shielded him from the elements.
Though the damp winds may tousle his hair, they are incapable of extinguishing the youthful sparkle in his eyes."

602722.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The pauldrons worn by Van Helsing. Its bold design accentuates the wearer's personality.
At the time, he hadn't realized that pursuing one's vision demands bearing heavy responsibility."

602723.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Van Helsing's wrist guard, stained with blood.
Even as the marsh envelops his figure, the young man draws his sword with swift alacrity, displaying not even a speck of hesitation."

602724.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Van Helsing's vows echoed with resolve.
It wasn't until darkness consumed him that he realized: Only actions taken from a position of power are considered true justice."

602731.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A veil worn by Ressa resembling that of a typical clergywoman, yet it holds a deeper meaning for her.
She ceaselessly smooths, folds, and tucks the edges into her white cap until the Bell of Tempus tolls."

602732.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Ressa Ambolia. It accompanied her over the long days and nights of separation, as she awaited someone's return.
Moonlight, gentle yet somewhat duplicitous, bathes her as she leans against the window, shedding tears, just as scripted."

602733.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Ressa's cherished promise ring, seemingly worn for ages.
The tiny silver ring worn on the middle finger silently declares love, yet by dawn, it becomes a shackle."

602734.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Ressa's cherished memories, strung together by countless moments of happiness.
In the end, the happiness they defended so vigorously was merely a ruse of fate, designed to trap them in the present."

"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The blazing crown of Agares the Beguiler, imbued with the primal power of War.
Bearing the sparks of hope, he brought them to the mortal realm, only to be judged by the gods as a thief."

602912.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The black robe of Agares the Beguiler, which suppresses his high-temperature scales. It is imbued with the primal power of War.
As the Flaming Chariot raced across the sky, he removed one of his own ribs, using it as kindling to cast the first ray of light."

602913.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> A ring forged from the blood of Agares the Beguiler, imbued with the primal power of War.
Iron nails pierce the chest, and hot blood stains the mountainside. Gazing down at the smoke billowing in mortal realms, he finally finds solace as he closes his eyes."

602914.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Agares the Beguiler, after being consumed by flames, left only a few feathers as proof of his existence in this world.
As he opens his eyes once more, wings grew from his spine, and his hunger drove him to gorge on entrails. Alas, he was never a hero, but a vulture who drank the blood of heroic memories."

602921.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The feathered crown discarded by Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
Renouncing himself to embrace death, his sole hope is to leave a trace of himself somewhere in the future."

602922.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The torn garment of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
The fervor which burned inside chest was not for the present, but for a future unbound from destiny."

602923.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring.</style> A ring forged from the blood of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
Blood and mind converged to birth a soul which could lead them forth. "This is faith; overbearing, yet ethereal.""

602924.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The amalgamation of deep despair and profound hope within Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
'Place down your sword, the future you seek is not elsewhere; it is right beneath your feet.'"

602931.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A crown that embodies Joan's resolve.
War is the lifeblood of civilization. Flowing through the corridors of history, it is unstoppable, nay inevitable."

602932.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A blood-stained suit of armor worn by Joan.
Leaning against the wall, the homeland lay behind her in ruins; gazing into the distance, the future lay before her in doubt."

602933.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Joan's signet ring, shaped like twin-peaks and engraved with the words "May Astolfo remain prosperous."
She leads all the lost souls unable to return home to the Motherland of nigh. "Through utter despair, hope springs anew.""

602934.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Joan's immortal past.
"Though yesterday has vanished and tomorrow is already known, how ought one navigate today?""

603411.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A hood that Clive would always wear before he turned into a beast.
"Children say I look scary, but admire me in battle. So I keep this thing on for them, I suppose. Until the grave calls me.""

603412.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The robe that Clive often wore.
The moonlight shone coolly, and the air filled with frost; The long night approached, yet the will to light was never lost."

603413.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The iron ring worn by Clive.
Alas, the abyss looms nigh. Proceed, and let darkness consume thee; Retreat, and let fear erode thy soul."

603414.m_mEquipDesc: "<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The Wolfsbane plant means something special to the Clive family.The ballad goes: "Wolfsbane blooms beneath the moon's soft grace; The promised home waits beyond the sky's embrace.""

603421.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A leather helmet sewn from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blood Beast.
Perhaps an illusion? The visage revealed by this Blackblood Beast appears to be in agony, yet somehow gives the impression of a grin."

603422.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A leather jacket sewn from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The wing membranes connecting their limbs are durable, yet flexible. As Blood Beasts evolve towards a form capable of flight, one must wonder: Where are they headed?"

603423.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> A ring crafted from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The bone smith who crafted this became haunted for seven nights, by horrific cries wailing in the darkness."

603424.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Amulet crafted from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The Bell Ringer melted the beast's seemingly impregnable hide instantaneously with a terrible heat, bringing inspiration to the artisans."

603431.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The dark iron helmet of Baphomet the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
Blood represents the gravity of memory, while souls are as free as the blue sky. It's not that they are grander, just less attached."

603432.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The heavy plate armor of Baphomet, the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"I gave up my body in pursuit of immortality, only to realize that the soul also ages.""

603433.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The dark iron ring of Baphomet the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"Once again, I find myself at your mercy. Perhaps this time, I should try finding credence in that distant prophecy?""

603434.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The rusty amulet of Baphomet, the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"Ashes beget ashes, and dust begets dust. Alas, life is but an anomaly, and all living memory perishes.""

603511.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Goldland's stylish cravat, clean and exquisite.
It still retains a faint scent, one that seemingly blends beauty and maturity."

603512.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Goldland's silk white shirt, completely spotless.
Though his elegance and grandeur may not be genuine, the effort placed into preserving purity is appreciable."

603513.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Goldland's golden ring, symbolizing wealth and status.
It represents the lofty status of the Landis family. From material to craftsmanship, it perfectly complements its current owner, and yet not once has he worn it."

603514.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Jewelry that never left Goldland's possession.
"Listen. This is all I have to leave you with. Adorn it, and seek your own freedom.""

603521.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
A sheer veil masks her gaze, yet fails to conceal the icy tear streaming down her cheek."

603522.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
Silken scaly wings drape over your shoulders and gently brush against your skin, providing you with a faint sense of solace."

603523.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Though Sheila the Firstborn's form has long since disintegrated, her icy ring still remains, imbued with the primal power of Plague.
The broken corpse marks the end of a cycle, while the ring heralds its dawn. "Abandoning the past shall lead to nowhere.""

603524.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Sheila the Firstborn's figure dissipated, thus breaking her final set of wings. It contains the primal power of Plague.
"Facing the abyss, I leap forward, if only to fill the chasms blocking your path ahead.""

"<style=EquipposHL>Ring.</style> A ring forged from the blood of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.

"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A blood-stained suit of armor worn by Joan.

603933.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Joan's signet ring, shaped like twin-peaks and engraved with the words "May Astolfo remain prosperous."

603934.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Joan's immortal past.
"Though yesterday has vanished and tomorrow is already known, how ought one navigate today?""

"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A hood that Clive would always wear before he turned into a beast.
"Children say I look scary, but admire me in battle. So I keep this thing on for them, I suppose. Until the grave calls me.""

604412.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The robe that Clive often wore.
The moonlight shone coolly, and the air filled with frost; The long night approached, yet the will to light was never lost."

604413.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The iron ring worn by Clive.
Alas, the abyss looms nigh. Proceed, and let darkness consume thee; Retreat, and let fear erode thy soul."

604414.m_mEquipDesc: "<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The Wolfsbane plant means something special to the Clive family.The ballad goes: "Wolfsbane blooms beneath the moon's soft grace; The promised home waits beyond the sky's embrace.""

604421.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A leather helmet sewn from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blood Beast.
Perhaps an illusion? The visage revealed by this Blackblood Beast appears to be in agony, yet somehow gives the impression of a grin."

604422.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A leather jacket sewn from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The wing membranes connecting their limbs are durable, yet flexible. As Blood Beasts evolve towards a form capable of flight, one must wonder: Where are they headed?"

604423.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> A ring crafted from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The bone smith who crafted this became haunted for seven nights, by horrific cries wailing in the darkness."

604424.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Amulet crafted from the carcass of the Starfall Valley Blackblood Beast.
The Bell Ringer melted the beast's seemingly impregnable hide instantaneously with a terrible heat, bringing inspiration to the artisans."

604431.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The dark iron helmet of Baphomet the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
Blood represents the gravity of memory, while souls are as free as the blue sky. It's not that they are grander, just less attached."

604432.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The heavy plate armor of Baphomet, the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"I gave up my body in pursuit of immortality, only to realize that the soul also ages.""

604433.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The dark iron ring of Baphomet the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"Once again, I find myself at your mercy. Perhaps this time, I should try finding credence in that distant prophecy?""

604434.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The rusty amulet of Baphomet, the Soulless, Elder of the Bathory family.
"Ashes beget ashes, and dust begets dust. Alas, life is but an anomaly, and all living memory perishes.""

604511.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Goldland's stylish cravat, clean and exquisite.
It still retains a faint scent, one that seemingly blends beauty and maturity."

604512.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Goldland's silk white shirt, completely spotless.
Though his elegance and grandeur may not be genuine, the effort placed into preserving purity is appreciable."

604513.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Goldland's golden ring, symbolizing wealth and status.
It represents the lofty status of the Landis family. From material to craftsmanship, it perfectly complements its current owner, and yet not once has he worn it."

604514.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Jewelry that never left Goldland's possession.
"Listen. This is all I have to leave you with. Adorn it, and seek your own freedom.""

604521.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
A sheer veil masks her gaze, yet fails to conceal the icy tear streaming down her cheek."

604522.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
Silken scaly wings drape over your shoulders and gently brush against your skin, providing you with a faint sense of solace."

604523.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Though Sheila the Firstborn's form has long since disintegrated, her icy ring still remains, imbued with the primal power of Plague.
The broken corpse marks the end of a cycle, while the ring heralds its dawn. "Abandoning the past shall lead to nowhere.""

604524.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Sheila the Firstborn's figure dissipated, thus breaking her final set of wings. It contains the primal power of Plague.
"Facing the abyss, I leap forward, if only to fill the chasms blocking your path ahead.""

604531.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the crown of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
Cupping it in your palm, you lean in to listen, nearly making out the roar of the ocean. There seems to be a voice, too, but it is muffled by the foam."

604532.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the shattered scales of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
Bathed in the silver light of the moon, it seems one can glimpse a sorrowful past, or some unreachable distance, hidden in their luster."

604533.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The hardened tentacle tips of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, which retain the primal power of "Famine."
Reaching out to touch the light could be the path towards hope, or perhaps the start of an endless Abyss."

604534.m_mEquipDesc:

604713.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Piera's cherished ring, seemingly symbolizing a pact made with someone.

604722.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The pauldrons worn by Van Helsing. Its bold design accentuates the wearer's personality.

"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Van Helsing's wrist guard, stained with blood.
Even as the marsh envelops his figure, the young man draws his sword with swift alacrity, displaying not even a speck of hesitation."

604724.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Van Helsing's vows echoed with resolve.
It wasn't until darkness consumed him that he realized: Only actions taken from a position of power are considered true justice."

604731.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A veil worn by Ressa resembling that of a typical clergywoman, yet it holds a deeper meaning for her.
She ceaselessly smooths, folds, and tucks the edges into her white cap until the Bell of Tempus tolls."

604732.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Ressa Ambolia. It accompanied her over the long days and nights of separation, as she awaited someone's return.
Moonlight, gentle yet somewhat duplicitous, bathes her as she leans against the window, shedding tears, just as scripted."

604733.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Ressa's cherished promise ring, seemingly worn for ages.
The tiny silver ring worn on the middle finger silently declares love, yet by dawn, it becomes a shackle."

604734.m_mEquipDesc:

605613.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Goldland's golden ring, symbolizing wealth and status.
It represents the lofty status of the Landis family. From material to craftsmanship, it perfectly complements its current owner, and yet not once has he worn it."

605614.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Jewelry that never left Goldland's possession.
"Listen. This is all I have to leave you with. Adorn it, and seek your own freedom.""

605621.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
A sheer veil masks her gaze, yet fails to conceal the icy tear streaming down her cheek."

605622.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the iridescent wings of Sheila the Firstborn, it is imbued with the primal power of Plague.
Silken scaly wings drape over your shoulders and gently brush against your skin, providing you with a faint sense of solace."

605623.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Though Sheila the Firstborn's form has long since disintegrated, her icy ring still remains, imbued with the primal power of Plague.
The broken corpse marks the end of a cycle, while the ring heralds its dawn. "Abandoning the past shall lead to nowhere.""

605624.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Sheila the Firstborn's figure dissipated, thus breaking her final set of wings. It contains the primal power of Plague.
"Facing the abyss, I leap forward, if only to fill the chasms blocking your path ahead.""

605631.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> Crafted from the crown of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
Cupping it in your palm, you lean in to listen, nearly making out the roar of the ocean. There seems to be a voice, too, but it is muffled by the foam."

605632.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> Crafted from the shattered scales of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, it is imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
Bathed in the silver light of the moon, it seems one can glimpse a sorrowful past, or some unreachable distance, hidden in their luster."

605633.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> The hardened tentacle tips of Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, which retain the primal power of "Famine."
Reaching out to touch the light could be the path towards hope, or perhaps the start of an endless Abyss."

605634.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> A dorsal fin taken from Ranna, the Atoll Devourer, imbued with the primal power of "Famine."
'Facing the boundless sea, the shackles on my back deny me my only possession — freedom. And yet I embrace them willingly.'"

605711.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A headpiece worn by Piera that emanates a lambent glow.
Silk ribbons embroider the restless mind of the Bone Collector. Pray tell me, are white lies truly kind, or are they deception?"

605712.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Piera, stitched ornately.
Carefully, she collects the sorrows of the dead, folding each piece meticulously then stacking them on her shoulder, waiting for the pain to absorb into her."

605713.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Piera's cherished ring, seemingly symbolizing a pact made with someone.
Could internalizing one's pain be a form of deceit?"

605714.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Piera's collection of skulls, her constant companions.
Pristine white bones, each a testament to the girl's acts of redemption. She convinces herself this is a form of kindness."

605721.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The stylish cap worn by Isaac Van Helsing. On the pursuit of justice, it shielded him from the elements.
Though the damp winds may tousle his hair, they are incapable of extinguishing the youthful sparkle in his eyes."

605722.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The pauldrons worn by Van Helsing. Its bold design accentuates the wearer's personality.
At the time, he hadn't realized that pursuing one's vision demands bearing heavy responsibility."

605723.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Van Helsing's wrist guard, stained with blood.
Even as the marsh envelops his figure, the young man draws his sword with swift alacrity, displaying not even a speck of hesitation."

605724.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Van Helsing's vows echoed with resolve.
It wasn't until darkness consumed him that he realized: Only actions taken from a position of power are considered true justice."

605731.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A veil worn by Ressa resembling that of a typical clergywoman, yet it holds a deeper meaning for her.
She ceaselessly smooths, folds, and tucks the edges into her white cap until the Bell of Tempus tolls."

605732.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Ressa Ambolia. It accompanied her over the long days and nights of separation, as she awaited someone's return.
Moonlight, gentle yet somewhat duplicitous, bathes her as she leans against the window, shedding tears, just as scripted."

605733.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Ressa's cherished promise ring, seemingly worn for ages.
The tiny silver ring worn on the middle finger silently declares love, yet by dawn, it becomes a shackle."

605734.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Ressa's cherished memories, strung together by countless moments of happiness.
In the end, the happiness they defended so vigorously was merely a ruse of fate, designed to trap them in the present."

"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The blazing crown of Agares the Beguiler, imbued with the primal power of War.
Bearing the sparks of hope, he brought them to the mortal realm, only to be judged by the gods as a thief."

605912.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The black robe of Agares the Beguiler, which suppresses his high-temperature scales. It is imbued with the primal power of War.
As the Flaming Chariot raced across the sky, he removed one of his own ribs, using it as kindling to cast the first ray of light."

605913.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> A ring forged from the blood of Agares the Beguiler, imbued with the primal power of War.
Iron nails pierced the chest, and hot blood stained the mountainside. Gazing down at the smoke billowing in mortal realms, he finally found solace as he closed his eyes."

605914.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Agares the Beguiler, after being consumed by flames, left only a few feathers as proof of his existence in this world.
As he opens his eyes once more, wings grew from his spine, and his hunger drove him to gorge on entrails. Alas, he was never a hero, but a vulture who drank the blood of heroic memories."

605921.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> The feathered crown discarded by Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
Renouncing himself to embrace death, his sole hope is to leave a trace of himself somewhere in the future."

605922.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> The torn garment of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
The fervor which burned inside chest was not for the present, but for a future unbound from destiny."

605923.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring.</style> A ring forged from the blood of Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
Blood and mind converged to birth a soul which could lead them forth. "This is faith; overbearing, yet ethereal.""

605924.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> The amalgamation of deep despair and profound hope within Noah the Apostate, imbued with the primal power of Death.
'Place down your sword, the future you seek is not elsewhere; it is right beneath your feet.'"

605931.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Headgear</style> A crown that embodies Joan's resolve.
War is the lifeblood of civilization. Flowing through the corridors of history, it is unstoppable, nay inevitable."

605932.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Outfit</style> A blood-stained suit of armor worn by Joan.
Leaning against the wall, the homeland lay behind her in ruins; gazing into the distance, the future lay before her in doubt."

605933.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Ring</style> Joan's signet ring, shaped like twin-peaks and engraved with the words "May Astolfo remain prosperous."
She leads all the lost souls unable to return home to the Motherland of nigh. "Through utter despair, hope springs anew.""

605934.m_mEquipDesc:
"<style=EquipposHL>Amulet</style> Joan's immortal past.
"Though yesterday has vanished and tomorrow is already known, how ought one navigate today?""
